article.headline: Winthrop 67, Liberty 47
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Chris Gaynor scored 11 points and grabbed five rebounds, and Winthrop defeated Liberty 67-47 on Thursday. Winthrop (11-4, 5-0 Big South Conference) extended its conference winning streak to 23 games. Scott Draughn added 10 points and three rebounds for the Eagles. Winthrop held off a comeback attempt by the Flames (4-12, 1-3) with back-to-back plays from DeAndre Adams. He hit a 3 and had an assist on a Phillip Williams' dunk with 8:56 remaining to put the Eagles up 52-32. Larry Blair shot 9-of-12 from the free throw line and had 16 points to lead Liberty. Damien Hubbard added 11 points. The Eagles shot 44.9 percent (22-of-49) from the field while Liberty made just 32.6 percent (15-of-46) of its field goal attempts. Winthrop is 14-3 against Liberty.
